President Trump addressed a crowd at the signing of the 2018 Farm Bill, thanking members of Congress for their bipartisan work on the bill. He also discussed the importance of border security and his commitment to building a wall. Trump mentioned the need for welfare reform and announced that able-bodied adults without dependents will have to work or look for work to receive food stamps. Secretary of Agriculture Sonny Perdue also spoke at the event, expressing his gratitude for the passage of the bill. Trump then signed the Farm Bill into law.